A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the City of Chattahoochee Hills; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Chattahoochee Hills is a distinctive city located in the southwestern part of
3 Fulton County, Georgia, renowned for its picturesque countryside and sprawling farms,
4 offering residents and visitors a serene retreat from the urban bustle of nearby Atlanta; and
5 WHEREAS, during the 2006 Legislative Session, the Georgia General Assembly passed a
6 law allowing the Fulton County section of the area to incorporate as a city, thereby granting
7 local residents increased control over zoning and land use; and
8 WHEREAS, on June 19, 2007, the residents of the area overwhelmingly voted in favor of
9 incorporation by a margin of 83 percent to 17 percent, officially establishing the City of
10 Chattahoochee Hill Country within a 33,000-acre portion of Fulton County, with
11 incorporation taking effect on December 1, 2007; and
12 WHEREAS, the City of Chattahoochee Hills has since prioritized sustainable development,
13 focusing on preserving its natural landscapes while fostering economic opportunities and
14 modern infrastructure; and
