15 WHEREAS, the city is home to recreation areas such as the Chattahoochee Hills Eventing
16 Center and the Bear Creek Nature Center, which provide residents and visitors with
17 opportunities for hiking, horseback riding, and other outdoor activities; and
18 WHEREAS, agritourism and sustainable agriculture play a key role in the city's economy,
19 strengthening local farms and fostering a deeper appreciation for environmentally conscious
20 food production; and
21 WHEREAS, the City of Chattahoochee Hills is dedicated to enhancing the quality of life for
22 its residents through community-building efforts, economic development initiatives, and
23 support for local businesses; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable city be appropriately
25 honored during this special time.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body recognize and commend the City of Chattahoochee Hills for its
28 steadfast dedication to sustainability, environmental preservation, and community
29 development as well as extend best wishes for continued success.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
32 public and the press.
